snippet.textDisplay: was an unjust and stupid sacking. the only reason west ham unravelled after a great start to the season that saw them level with leicester, was roberto-that terrible goalkeeper. fabianski got injured. and from the moment roberto deputised west ham kept losing. then they actually replaced him with a training goalkeeper which instantly led to three wins in a row. but then that keeper got injured. with fabianski back in this game, pellegrini would only have needed a few gqmes to get west ham back on track. this was all entirely to do with the goalkeeper., without a reliable keeper the defense  gets edgy. look at the difference alison made to liverpool. roberto should have been more quickly got rid of though. but this firing of pellegrini shows that the club hierachy really have no idea what was happening at west ham. if i can see it, then why the hell couldnt pellegrini's superiors? pellegrini was too good for west ham. he was a manager who could have actually got them european football regularly, nailing down a sixth position in the premier league table. and it is a good west ham squad, felipe anderson, antonio, and they've got a great keeper in fabianski, and a real team leader in noble. now they will replace him with a relegation escape artist who has no abilities to propel a team into the top six or top four. pellegrini plus saudi money transformed man city to a bigger club than man united, to premier league champions. i actually think pellegrini's man city were better than pep guardiola's man city. look at how pellegrini orchestrated the anihilation of fergerson's man united. although they are close to relegation zone, this was a scared reaction to fire pellegrini. west ham would never have been relegated.
